## What OVR-SmoothTracking Actually Does

The BOOTH description is the key: **"interfering with SteamVR's movement prediction"** — not filtering the pose, literally manipulating `vecVelocity` and `vecAngularVelocity`.

The OpenVR-InputEmulator source confirms this pattern. Their `MotionCompensationVelAccMode::SetZero` mode:
```cpp
setVelToZero = true;
setAccToZero = true;
setAngVelToZero = true;
setAngAccToZero = true;
```
...and their `LinearApproximation` mode (which DOES try to derive velocity from position deltas) **still zeros angular velocity entirely**. The comment in the code:
> *"Predicting acceleration values leads to a very jittery experience. Also, the lighthouse driver does not send acceleration values anyway, so why care?"*

## What the Fix Looks Like

OVR-SmoothTracking's approach is the simplest and most effective for HMD use: **zero the velocities entirely when smoothing is enabled**.

```cpp
// After applying One Euro filter to position/rotation:
if (m_smoothingEnabled && m_isHMD) {
    // Zero out all velocity signals.
    // SteamVR's compositor will use the smoothed pose as-is,
    // with no forward prediction overshoot.
    pose.vecVelocity[0] = pose.vecVelocity[1] = pose.vecVelocity[2] = 0.0;
    pose.vecAngularVelocity[0] = pose.vecAngularVelocity[1] = pose.vecAngularVelocity[2] = 0.0;
    pose.vecAcceleration[0] = pose.vecAcceleration[1] = pose.vecAcceleration[2] = 0.0;
    pose.vecAngularAcceleration[0] = pose.vecAngularAcceleration[1] = pose.vecAngularAcceleration[2] = 0.0;
}
```

The tradeoff: at very low smoothing values (say 1%) this is basically a no-op on the pose but it does eliminate last-millisecond compositor prediction. For HMD that's actually fine since the main goal is removing jitter, not preserving sub-frame prediction precision.

A better version (consistent velocity instead of zero) would derive `vecVelocity` from the **smoothed position delta**:
```cpp
// Finite diff on filtered output — consistent with what compositor will predict
if (m_hasLastSmoothedPose) {
    float dt = currentTime - m_lastSmoothedTime;
    if (dt > 0.0001f) {
        pose.vecVelocity[0] = (smoothedPos.x - m_lastSmoothedPos.x) / dt;
        pose.vecVelocity[1] = (smoothedPos.y - m_lastSmoothedPos.y) / dt;
        pose.vecVelocity[2] = (smoothedPos.z - m_lastSmoothedPos.z) / dt;
    }
    // Angular velocity: zero it. Deriving from quaternion delta is unstable.
    pose.vecAngularVelocity[0] = pose.vecAngularVelocity[1] = pose.vecAngularVelocity[2] = 0.0;
}
```
